{% import "macros/paths" as paths %}
Read the symbol at line 42 (follows symlink → body):

    Read `{{ paths.at_line("<file>", 42) }}`

Directly edit a symbol at a known line:

    Read → Edit `{{ paths.at_line("<file>", 42) }}`

    Note: at-line is symlinked directly to the full symbol body, including docstring and decorators

Insert code at known location:

    echo 'fn foo() { }' >> {{ paths.lines("<file>", "10") }} # append after line 10
    echo 'fn bar() { }' > {{ paths.at_line("<file>", 42) }} # replace (splice) full symbol at line 42 with new function

    Read → Edit `{{ paths.sym("<file>", "Foo", ext) }}` → Insert code before/after existing symbol

Line range access (escape hatch — prefer symbol-targeted access):

    Read → Edit `{{ paths.lines("<file>") }}` (full file)
    Read → Edit `{{ paths.lines("<file>", "10-20") }}` (range)

List symbols by kind:

    ls {{ paths.by_kind("<file>", "fn") }}
